header.gameNote: OUTRIGGER RAINBOW CLASSIC AT HONOLULU HI

article.headline: Iowa State 83, South Florida 74
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Rahshon Clark had 19 points to lead four Cyclones in double figure as Iowa State beat South Florida 83-74 Wednesday night in the final game of the opening round of the Rainbow Classic. Will Blalock had 16 points and 10 assists for Iowa State (7-3). Curtis Stinson added 13 points for the Cyclones and John Neal 11. McHugh Mattis led all scorers with 23 points for South Florida (5-4), shooting a tournament record 10-for-10 from the field. James Holmes added 20 points and Melvin Buckley 19 for the Bulls. South Florida took a 57-55 lead on Holmes' 3-pointer from the right side with 9:35 remaining in the game. But back-to-back Bulls turnovers and 3-pointers from Iowa State's Stinson and Jiri Hubalek keyed a 10-0 Cyclone run and South Florida would get no closer than four down the stretch. South Florida shot 61.4 percent from the field (27-of-44) but committed 25 turnovers in the game. South Florida led by as many as 12 points with 4:31 left in the first half. But Iowa State closed out the first with an 18-2 run, capped by Clark's 3-pointer from the left wing at the first half buzzer, to take a 41-37 lead.
